- https://github.com/xdslproject/xdsl/pull/5683
- https://github.com/xdslproject/xdsl/pull/5684

(2) get rid of exo dialect

- https://github.com/xdslproject/xdsl/pull/4371 (not merged yet! needs to be redone) -> attempt to add lowering for `memref.reinterpret_cast` and `memref.cast` in the upstream `convert-memref-to-ptr` pass. building block for the larger effort below.
    - `memref.subview`: https://mlir.llvm.org/docs/Dialects/MemRef/#memrefsubview-memrefsubviewop
    - `memref.reinterpret_cast`: https://mlir.llvm.org/docs/Dialects/MemRef/#memrefreinterpret_cast-memrefreinterpretcastop

---

option A: raw pointers (current, single-stage)

`ConvertMemRefToLLVM` goes directly from exo ops to LLVM pointer arithmetic in one step.

- `exo.read %buf[i, j]` â†’ cast memref to `llvm.ptr` â†’ `gep(ptr, i*stride0 + j*stride1)` â†’ `llvm.load`
- problem: offset is baked into the pointer. `exo.window` (subview) computes a new pointer via GEP and casts it back to a memref, but the offset is lost. this means:
    - can't invert a window operation unless the offset is statically known in the type
    - incompatible with standard MLIR memref semantics, making upstream merging harder

---

option B: memref descriptors (standard MLIR, two-stage)

Splits lowering into two clean stages:

1. exo â†’ memref: `exo.{read,assign,window}` â†’ `memref.{load,store,subview}` (code exists in `convert_tensor_ref.py`, currently unused / not wired into pipeline)
2. memref â†’ ptr/llvm: `memref.*` â†’ `ptr/llvm.*` (upstream xdsl's `convert-memref-to-ptr`, extended by PR #4371)

- functions take descriptor structs `{base_ptr, offset, sizes[], strides[]}`
- keeps offset/stride metadata alongside the pointer
- makes subview/window trivially invertible (negate the offset)
- matches upstream xdsl/MLIR conventions
- if the offset is in the type, inversion is trivial. otherwise panic (out of scope for now)

---

pipeline considerations

Current pipeline in `main.py`:

```
partial lowering â†’ optimize (canonicalize + CSE) â†’ full lowering â†’ optimize (canonicalize + CSE)
```

Full lowering currently runs: `ConvertBLASAllocPass` â†’ `ConvertMemRefToLLVM` â†’ `ConvertAVX2Pass` â†’ `ConvertBLASPass` â†’ `ConvertScfToCf` â†’ `ReconcileUnrealizedCastsPass`

To adopt option B: insert `ConvertTensorRefPass` before `ConvertMemRefToLLVM` (replaces exoâ†’llvm with exoâ†’memref), then keep a memrefâ†’llvm pass after it. Need to consider ordering relative to BLAS/AVX2 passes.

---

goals

- do pointer arithmetic at creation time (window/subview), so reads are just `load(base_ptr + pre-computed offset)`
- track offsets explicitly so inversion is possible
- match upstream MLIR conventions for merging with xdsl

longer-term: exo emits LLVM IR (not just C), xdsl gets proper memref descriptor support, compile exo â†’ xdsl â†’ llvmlite and benchmark real workloads
